The paper deals with the challenge of de-duplication in data integration, which is a common problem in databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The authors propose a system that uses machine learning techniques to automatically learn hash functions, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The system also uses a hierarchical tree structure, which is a common data structure in computer science and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the system aims to optimize recall and efficiency, which is a common problem in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
